ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Ruff-Light Trail Learning Test - Total number of correct choices for trials 2 through 10; if the test is mastered prior to trial 10, full credit of 15 is given for each trial that was not administered and the Number Correct boxes for Trials 2 to 10 are summed horizontally.
Ruff-Light Trail Learning Test - Total number of trials administered before the task is mastered (i.e., completion of two consecutive, trials without error)
Ruff-Light Trail Learning Test - Number correct on the 60-minute delayed recall trial - Delayed Correct
Ruff-Light Trail Learning Test - Number of errors committed on the 60-minute delayed recall trial - Delayed Errors
